(a) The partial molar volume of a component is given by:
V1 = V1(m) + V1(e)
where V1(m) is the molar volume of pure 1 and V1(e) is the partial molar excess volume of component 1.

For an equimolar mixture, x1 = x2 = 0.5.

V1 = RT/(ρ1x1){1 + a0/(ρ1x1) + a1(1 - x1)}
= RT/(0.971 g cm^-3)(0.5 mol/1)(1 g/cm^3)(1 mol/1000 g){1 + a0/(ρ1x1) + a1(1 - x1)}
= RT/(0.971 g cm^-3)(0.5 mol/1)(1 g/cm^3)(1 mol/1000 g){1 + -2.4697 cm^3 mol^-1 / (0.971 g cm^-3)(0.5 mol/1)(1 g/cm^3)(1 mol/1000 g) + 0.0608 cm^3 mol^-1 (1 - 0.5)}
= RT/(0.971 g cm^-3)(0.5 mol/1)(1 g/cm^3)(1 mol/1000 g){1 - 0.0608 / (0.4855) + 0.0608}
= RT/(0.971 g cm^-3)(0.5 mol/1)(1 g/cm^3)(1 mol/1000 g)(0.8751)
= 0.0378 + 0.0067 = 0.0445 L mol^-1

V2 = RT/(ρ2x2){1 + a0/(ρ2x2) + a1(1 - x2)}
= RT/(0.863 g cm^-3)(0.5 mol/1)(1 g/cm^3)(1 mol/1000 g){1 + a0/(ρ2x2) + a1(1 - x2)}
= RT/(0.863 g cm^-3)(0.5 mol/1)(1 g/cm^3)(1 mol/1000 g){1 - 2.4697 / (0.863)(0.5) + 0.0608 (1 - 0.5)}
= RT/(0.863 g cm^-3)(0.5 mol/1)(1 g/cm^3)(1 mol/1000 g){1 - 2.8699 + 0.0608}
= RT/(0.863 g cm^-3)(0.5 mol/1)(1 g/cm^3)(1 mol/1000 g)(-1.8699)
= -0.0238 - 0.0061 = -0.0299 L mol^-1

The partial molar volumes for propionic acid and tetrahydropyran at an equimolar mixture are 0.0445 L mol^-1 and -0.0299 L mol^-1, respectively.

